<raw><![CDATA[ YOKOHAMA, Nov 14 (Reuters) - Leaders of the 21-memberAsia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) forum issued a statementon Sunday, calling for balanced growth in the fast-growing regionand promising to refrain from competitive devaluation ofcurrencies. "We will move toward more market-determined exchange ratesystems and enhance exchange rate flexibility to reflectunderlying economic fundamentals and will refrain fromcompetitive devaluation of currencies," the statement issued bythe Japanese foreign ministry said.(Reporting by Yoko Nishikawa and Yoko Kubota; Editing by EdDavies)             ]]></raw>
